PathOfBuilding.Notes:
^xFFFF77^xB97123YouTube guide^7^7: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XjMtzJVwaDg
^xB97123LAB POINTS^7
Call of the Ancestors (warcry recovery) Ancestral Endurance (3 endurance) Ancestral Defiance (defiance node) Toughened Skin (action speed can't be slowed + double body armour)
^xB97123QUICK NOTES ABOUT BUILD^7
-Only use Trinity when you have gloves with conversion. (this will be 5th or 6th link and you drop the fire convert node then) -Momentum feels nice for campaign for attack speed, but melee physical or pulverise would be more damage. -Make sure to target behind bosses for Volcanic Fissure of Snaking, you can hit 3 times (with quality) - auto targeting is less consistent. -Normal Lab farming for Volcanic Fissure is about 1 in 11 runs, it might be easier to buy it if in trade league, however you can also just level as Sunder until Merc lab if you want. -Before you get clusters, leech is a problem for Volcanic Fissure, there is no easy to access attack leech nearby on the tree. Clever Thief is a cheap annoint that grants attack and mana leech. -Dealing with mana early is mostly mana potion + cannibalistic rite and mastery, life mastery for "15% skills mana cost as life instead" is also nice early. If you really don't want to deal with mana at all, consider using Lifetap until you get leech.
^xB97123AXE VS MACE^7
-Most of the game this build uses Axes, they have a lot more attack speed and passives are generally better than maces. -The rune enchant "Gain 50% of weapon physical as extra damage of each element" is a game changer however, it adds a TON of damage endgame, though this costs 4 power runes. -Once you get the enchant Maces become quite a bit better, but it's more of a minmax endgame build option.
